{
  "text": "Rat fat-pad ECs (RFPECs) were cultured at 37°C with 5% CO2 in Dulbecco's modified Eagle medium (DMEM, Invitrogen) supplemented with 10% fetal bovine serum (FBS; Invitrogen) and 1% penicillin-streptomycin. Cells between passages 22 and 30 were then seeded onto glass-bottom dishes (MatTek) until confluence (2 to ϳ3 days), unless indicated otherwise [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
